article.headline: South Carolina 57, East Carolina 53
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Carlos Powell hit a layup and Tarence Kinsey made two free throws in the final minutes, leading South Carolina to a 57-53 victory over East Carolina on Monday in the first round of the Coors Classic. Kinsey led the Gamecocks (6-2) with 13 points and Powell added 12. Mike Cook led East Carolina with a game-high 24 points and Corey Rouse had 13 rebounds. East Carolina (4-6) led for most of the second half, until Rocky Trice hit a pair of free throws and tied the game 49-49. Seconds later, Trice stole the Ball from Cook, allowing Powell to hit a layup with 2:56. East Carolina cut the lead to 1 on a Corey Rouse free throw, but couldn't get closer. The Gamecocks finished with a 5-2 spurt, topped by Kinsey's foul shots. East Carolina dominated the board 45-31, but were held to 35 percent shooting.
